/// ExitError — BEAM process exit signal.
///
/// Raised when an Erlang function exits via `exit(Reason)`.
/// The original exit reason is available in the error details.
///
/// See: ADR 0028 §1 (Exception mapping)
///
/// ## Examples
/// ```beamtalk
/// [Erlang erlang exit: #killed] on: ExitError do: [:e | e message]
/// ```
BEAMError subclass: ExitError

